# Django Code Style Rules

## General
- Use type hints where appropriate
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Write docstrings for classes and functions

## Django Specific
- Use Django's built-in features (forms, models, views)
- Prefer class-based views over function-based views
- Use Django's ORM instead of raw SQL
- Use Django's settings for configuration
- Follow Django's naming conventions

## Code Organization
- Keep views thin, business logic in services/utils
- Use separate files for models, views, forms, serializers
- Group related functionality in apps

## Error Handling
- Use try-except blocks for API calls
- Return meaningful error messages
- Log errors appropriately

## Testing
- Write tests for critical functionality
- Use Django's TestCase for unit tests




